WEBVTT

00:00:00.240 --> 00:00:07.120
They get so excited about the modeling that they forget that actually we have to like

00:00:07.120 --> 00:00:12.400
make value or there is no reason that we exist. We're just becoming an expense.

00:00:13.680 --> 00:00:18.959
So I've had to have those conversations before. I know this is exciting, but there is a balance

00:00:18.959 --> 00:00:26.639
between figuring out a really cool way of doing this and giving real value without taking too

00:00:26.639 --> 00:00:30.559
much time. Those are conversations. And depending on the person,

00:00:31.600 --> 00:00:35.840
there are just people that would love to be in academia but are not.

00:00:39.680 --> 00:00:47.680
So some of the PhDs I have had more of that with. And I think that's just because,

00:00:47.680 --> 00:00:49.759
like, you've been in school forever. That is what you do.

00:00:50.320 --> 00:00:57.439
So I had one other thought because we're still talking.

00:00:59.200 --> 00:01:06.639
Getting people to present their results is useful. But I've had to coach multiple people being like,

00:01:06.639 --> 00:01:11.199
OK, remember who's in the audience. You're talking to the CEO. Is he going to care about this?

00:01:11.919 --> 00:01:18.080
No. He cares about his financials showing this, this, and this. So how can you relate this back

00:01:18.400 --> 00:01:20.320
instead of spoon feeding it, though? Like,

00:01:20.959 --> 00:01:25.440
you've got to get them to actually understand how to do that, which takes time.

